      "content": "Magnesium supplements will not prevent vitamin D toxicity, and self-managing a 50,000 IU daily dose poses severe health risks even for a short two-week period. Without knowing your specific blood levels, taking such a high dose just increases the likelihood of dangerous side effects like kidney damage. The safest approach is to consume a standard daily supplement through reliable over-the-counter options or pharmacy brands until you can afford a medical consultation for a proper blood test. Given your symptoms, a moderate, consistent dose is far safer than attempting a risky \"loading\" phase without supervision.",
